properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 17 at 6:06AM CST until January 18 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...HEAVY SNOW THIS AFTERNOON INTO SATURDAY...

.Increasing clouds has led to increasing temperatures. Wind chill
values have improved this morning, although a few around 25 below
will be possible through mid morning.

Snow will develop through the day and spread north and east this
afternoon into the evening, becoming widespread tonight. The snow
will last into Saturday but will decrease from southwest to
northeast through the day into the evening. Total snowfall for
most areas will be from 5 to 10 inches, with higher amounts
expected along the higher terrain of the North Shore. In addition
to the snow, gusty southerly winds will occur today into this
evening then strong northwest winds will occur Saturday. The wind
will cause blowing and drifting snow, especially on Saturday.

* WHAT...Heavy snow will then develop through the day into
Saturday. A brief period of freezing drizzle may occur as well
today. Total snow accumulations of 5 to 8 inches and ice
accumulations of a light glaze. Winds gusting as high as 35 mph
today and especially Saturday.

* WHERE...South Itasca, North Cass, Koochiching, North Itasca,
South Cass, Crow Wing, Northern Aitkin and South Aitkin
Counties. This includes the Tribal Lands of the Mille Lacs
Band, East Lake and, Big Sandy Lake areas and the Bois Forte
Band, Deer Creek and, Nett Lake areas.

* WHEN...From noon today to 6 PM CST Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Patchy blowing snow
could significantly reduce visibility. The hazardous
conditions could impact the morning or evening commute. The
cold wind chills as low as 25 below zero could cause frostbite
on exposed skin in as little as 30 minutes.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1.
Road conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM NOON TODAY TO 6 PM CST SATURDAY... ...WIND CHILL ADVISORY HAS EXPIRED
